description.narrative: Oxfam Denmark is the intermediary for the AGIR Programme which is a programme on governance funded by the Embassies of Sweden and the Netherlands, being implemented by Oxfam Denmark since 2010. The main objective of the programme is #to ensure active citizens and strong and vibrant civil society that influences and participates in democratic process contributing for more responsive governance, deepened democracy, gender equity and human rights in Mozambique#. The programme was extended for the next 6 years (2015-2020), for the first 3 years (2015-17) to be renewed for the other 3 years (2018-2020). The current phase has 4 themes: 1) Extractive industry; 2) Strengthening Parliaments; 3) Monitoring of public services; and, 4. Freedom of expression. According to AICE/AGIR proposal document the programme will be implemented in four provinces: Tete (Moatize and Tete City), Nampula (Moma, Nacala and Nampula City),Zambézia (Alto Molócué, Mocuba and Quelimane City) and Cabo Delgado (Montepuez, Palma and Pemba City). These provinces are also Oxfam IBIS#s priorities areas. The AICE/AGIR programme will be implemented by 15 partners (13 at national level and 2 at province level) along the country. The budget for the six year of the programme is SEK 200.000.000,00. The first SEK 100.000.000 will be allocatedto the period 2015-2017 and last the SEK 100.000.000 are related to the period 2018-2020.

participating-org.narrative: Oxfam Novib is one of the 17 national affiliates of the Oxfam International Confederation. It started life in 1956 as the Netherlands Organisation for International Assistance (Novib), and joined forces with Oxfam in 1994. Working together in confederation, the Oxfam affiliates can speak with one clear and compelling voice on issues of global concern: climate change, health and education forall, agriculture, trade, and conflicts and emergencies. Oxfam established this country office to support local organizations and projects. Through this local office Oxfam Novib directly contributes towards this project’s implementation.
